# Create vector of forward reads
forward_reads <- list.files(raw_fastqs_path, pattern = "*_1.fastq.gz", full.names = TRUE)  

# Normalize Path
forward_reads <- normalizePath(forward_reads)

# Intuition Checks 
head(forward_reads)
## [1] "/local/workdir/xw722/CDI/16S_raw_data/SRR13060060_1.fastq.gz"
## [2] "/local/workdir/xw722/CDI/16S_raw_data/SRR13060061_1.fastq.gz"
## [3] "/local/workdir/xw722/CDI/16S_raw_data/SRR13060062_1.fastq.gz"
## [4] "/local/workdir/xw722/CDI/16S_raw_data/SRR13060065_1.fastq.gz"
## [5] "/local/workdir/xw722/CDI/16S_raw_data/SRR13060066_1.fastq.gz"
## [6] "/local/workdir/xw722/CDI/16S_raw_data/SRR13060067_1.fastq.gz"
# Intuition check #2: We should have fewer reads in the forward vector than in total 
stopifnot(length(forward_reads) < length(list.files(raw_fastqs_path)))

# Create a vector of reverse reads 
reverse_reads <- list.files(raw_fastqs_path, pattern = "*_2.fastq.gz", full.names = TRUE)

# Normalize Path
reverse_reads <- normalizePath(reverse_reads)

# Intuition Checks
head(reverse_reads)
## [1] "/local/workdir/xw722/CDI/16S_raw_data/SRR13060060_2.fastq.gz"
## [2] "/local/workdir/xw722/CDI/16S_raw_data/SRR13060061_2.fastq.gz"
## [3] "/local/workdir/xw722/CDI/16S_raw_data/SRR13060062_2.fastq.gz"
## [4] "/local/workdir/xw722/CDI/16S_raw_data/SRR13060065_2.fastq.gz"
## [5] "/local/workdir/xw722/CDI/16S_raw_data/SRR13060066_2.fastq.gz"
## [6] "/local/workdir/xw722/CDI/16S_raw_data/SRR13060067_2.fastq.gz"
# Intuition check #2: Need to have equal number of forward and reverse files 
stopifnot(length(reverse_reads) == length(forward_reads))

#Visualize and inspect quality of the sequences #see the quality of the raw reads befire we trim our sequences

#randomly select 12 samples
random_samples <- sample(1:length(reverse_reads), size = 12)
random_samples
##  [1]  59 104  49 115  92 168   8 136 133  55 100 144
#forward quality plot
forward_filteredQual_plot_12 <-
  plotQualityProfile(forward_reads[random_samples]) +
